- Is Relevant: True
- Reason: The trial (NETTER-2) evaluated Lutathera plus long-acting octreotide versus high-dose long-acting octreotide as first-line therapy for patients with advanced, well-differentiated, grade 2 or 3 GEP-NETs. The patient has metastatic GEP-NET (small intestine, G1, liver metastases) and is considering further therapy after initial resection and ongoing somatostatin analog therapy, which aligns with the context of the trial.
- Relevant Sections:
  - The trial compared Lutathera + long-acting octreotide to high-dose long-acting octreotide for first-line treatment of advanced GEP-NET grade 2 or 3.
